<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 13 at 7:13PM CST  by NWS Lake Charles</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of west central Rapides
and northeastern Vernon Parishes through 745 PM CST...
At 713 PM CST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Lacamp, or 7 miles east of Slagle, moving northeast at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Clifton and Simpson.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CST for central and
west central Louisiana.</instruction>
